{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-8291"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Activities of collection agencies and credit bureaus (corporate/compliance intelligence)"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "8291"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-citation "ISIC Rev.4 8291 explanatory note: \"activities of collection agencies and credit bureaus\" (https://unstats.un.org/unsd/classifications/Econ/Detail/EN/27/8291)"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :compliance/corporate-intelligence
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:transparency :regulatory-transparency :accountability :data-sovereignty]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :disclosure-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics false
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:identity :audit-ledger]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "Dossier-LLM ⊣ DisclosureGovernor (dossier.policy, six checks: scope-gate ·
  source-basis · licensed-disclosure · confidence-floor · high-stakes-gate ·
  correction-requests-always-escalate), langgraph StateGraph
  (dossier.operation/build-graph), append-only audit ledger
  (dossier.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore/DatomicStore parity).
  Four governed disclosure ops (:disclosure/query,
  :disclosure/screen-name, :disclosure/ownership-chain,
  :disclosure/relationship-check), each gated by a licensed-tier check with
  no bypass. A phase 0→3 staged-autonomy gate (dossier.phase) sits on top
  of the governor and can only ever narrow, never widen, what the governor
  already allowed. Schema is structurally scoped to professional/official-
  capacity public-record facts only — no field exists anywhere for
  private-life data (dossier.store's schema + dossier.policy's scope-gate
  as defense in depth).

  Real (not stubbed) integrations: dossier.kotobase-identity + dossier.edge
  (cacao/cacao-mint/cbor/base58) mint this actor's own CACAO/DID identity
  against net-kotobase (ADR-2607192200); dossier.web-search calls
  net-kotobase's live web-search client; dossier.gleif and
  dossier.companies-house chain real fallbacks onto the GLEIF LEI Registry
  API (no key required) and the UK Companies House public data API
  (free key) so lookups can be answered from live public registries, not
  only seeded fixtures — local/seeded data always wins when present, so
  the live fallback can only add coverage, never override an existing
  answer; dossier.sec-edgar, dossier.commoncrawl, dossier.houjin-bangou and
  dossier.lei-site-archive add further live/public-source lookups. 165
  tests / 620 assertions green (`clojure -M:dev:test`), demo runnable
  end-to-end (`clojure -M:dev:run`). This is the corporate-intelligence
  provider four other fleet blueprints
  (cloud-itonami-isic-6910/6810/6499/6512/6419) already call for KYC/
  sanctions screening via :disclosure/screen-name."}
